Kraken Motorsports Website – Build Specification for GitHub AI

Project Overview
Create a lightweight, fast, modern website for Kraken Motorsports, a VR racing‑rig experience launching soon. The site should function as a pre‑launch hub: showcasing the brand, explaining the concept, collecting interest, and preparing for Founders Pass sales. No backend hardware integration is needed yet—just clean structure and placeholder components.

The site should feel:
- bold  
- dark‑cyan themed  
- slightly chaotic sticker‑bomb aesthetic  
- modern motorsport energy  
- clean, fast, and responsive  

Think: esports team + arcade attraction + VR racing.

---

Core Requirements

1. Landing Page
A single‑scroll hero section with:
- Kraken logo  
- Tagline: “The Kraken Rig Experience — Coming Soon”  
- Dark cyan + black color palette  
- Subtle animated tentacle or glitch effect (CSS only, no heavy JS)  
- CTA buttons:
  - “Join the Discord”
  - “Reserve a Founders Pass” (placeholder link)
  - “Follow the Build”

2. About the Kraken Rig (Pre‑Launch Version)
A section explaining the concept:
- What the Kraken Rig is  
- VR racing + public leaderboard  
- Lounge placement concept  
- “Build‑in‑public” story  
- No hardware images needed—use placeholder mockups

3. Leaderboard Preview
A static mock leaderboard:
- Table with fake names + lap times  
- Styled like a motorsport timing screen  
- Placeholder data only  
- Should look like it will eventually update live

4. Founders Pass Section
A section describing:
- What the Founders Pass is  
- Perks list  
- Limited slots  
- Placeholder “Reserve” button  
- No payment integration yet

5. Sticker‑Bomb / Branding Gallery
A grid of:
- Kraken logo variations  
- Tentacle patterns  
- Color palette  
- UI mockups  
- Placeholder images allowed  

This is purely aesthetic.

6. Countdown Component
A simple JS countdown timer to a placeholder launch date:
- “Kraken Rig Launches In: XX Days”  
- Editable date in code

7. Contact / Social Section
Links to:
- Discord  
- Instagram  
- TikTok  
- Email placeholder  

---

Technical Requirements

Framework
Use Next.js or Astro (developer’s choice) with:
- Fast static generation  
- Clean component structure  
- Easy future expansion  

Styling
Use TailwindCSS with:
- Custom dark‑cyan theme  
- Motorsport‑style typography  
- Optional CSS animations for tentacles/glitch effects  

Structure
Pages/components needed:
- / (landing page)
- /founders (Founders Pass info)
- /leaderboard (static preview)
- /branding (gallery)
- /contact

No backend required yet
Use:
- Static JSON for leaderboard mock data  
- Placeholder links for payments  
- Placeholder images for rig mockups  

Future‑proofing
Write components so they can later accept:
- Real leaderboard API data  
- Real session tracking  
- Real payment links  
- Real rig photos  

---

Tone + Aesthetic Guidelines
- Dark, neon‑cyan, high‑contrast  
- Clean motorsport UI elements  
- Occasional chaotic sticker‑bomb clusters  
- Kraken mascot integrated subtly  
- Esports‑style typography  
- Smooth animations, not heavy or laggy  

---

Deliverables
- Fully responsive website  
- Clean component structure  
- Placeholder content ready to be swapped  
- Easy to deploy on Vercel or Netlify  
- README explaining:
  - How to edit mock data  
  - How to change branding  
  - How to update countdown date  

